        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 12:45AM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 1245 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Huntsville, or 10 miles northeast of Mocksville,
moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Winston-Salem, Kernersville, Clemmons, Bermuda Run, Huntsville,
Lewisville, Summerfield, Stokesdale, Walkertown, and Rural Hall.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
